{comment: Verse 1}
[C]I know a guy that's got a lot to lose.
[F]He's a pretty nice fellow but he's kind of confused.
[C]He's got muscles in his head that ain't never been used.
[G]Thinks he own half of this town.

[C]Starts drinking heavy, gets a big red nose.
[F]Beats his old lady with a rubber hose,
[C]then he takes her out to dinner and buys her new clothes.
[G]That's the w[C]ay that the world goes 'round.

{comment: Chorus}
[C]That's the way that the world goes 'round.
[F]You're up one day, the next you're down.
[C]It's a half an inch of water and you think you're gonna drown.
[G]That's the way that the w[C]orld goes 'round.

